# SEO skill (pointer)

Canonical: [`/skills/seo/SKILL.md`](../../skills/seo/SKILL.md). Read it before acting.

Key points:

- **Gatekeeper for on-page SEO and entity graph** — titles, meta descriptions, canonicals, hreflang, OG/Twitter, JSON-LD, robots, sitemap, keyword framing, internal links. Not a page author (that is `page`), not a performance skill (that is `performance-check`).
- **Normative docs**: `docs/Andetag SEO Manual.md` (keyword + schema doctrine), `docs/Tone of Voice.md` (copy constraints — em dash U+2014 prohibited, banned word list), `docs/url-migration-policy.md` (URL architecture), `docs/meta-texts-catalog.md` (title + description source), `docs/migration-exceptions.md` (EX-0015 `/en/` hub, EX-0016 Berlin English → Stockholm English canonical, EX-0017 Museum + LocalBusiness for AggregateRating, EX-0019 utställning spelling).
- **Runtime contract**: `page-shell-registry.ts` (canonical + hreflang), `seo.ts` (`CANONICAL_HOST`, `OG_SITE_NAME`, BCP47/OG locale), `schema-org.ts` (entity graph), `SiteLayout.astro` (emission).
- **Locale parity**: Stockholm `sv+en`, Berlin `en+de`. No cross-location hreflang on topic pages. Berlin English story shells canonicalise to Stockholm English (EX-0016) — not a bug.
- **Source integrity (non-negotiable)**: no fabricated URLs, keywords, ratings, prices, or schema fields. `page-shell-meta.json` / `stockholm-*.ts` / `schema-org.ts` are sources of truth; `site-html/` is legacy scrape, reference only. If the catalog doesn't have it, don't ship it — draft the catalog row first.
- **Audit dimensions (§B)**: title, meta description, canonical, hreflang, OG+Twitter, robots, JSON-LD, internal links, sitemap. Report line template in §Verification.
- **OSS lineage**: structural inspiration only from MIT-licensed `coreyhaines31/marketingskills/skills/seo-audit` and `JeffLi1993/seo-audit-skill`. Nothing vendored; substance is the ANDETAG docs.
- **Escalate**: changes to `CANONICAL_HOST` / `OG_SITE_NAME` / hreflang attribute mapping; new keyword outside SEO Manual §2 without GSC support; new schema type not in §6; `noindex` addition to an indexable shell; Rich Results strategy changes; Tone of Voice edge cases; Berlin pre-opening scope violations.
